snippet.textDisplay: Microwave ovens heat by vibrating the water molecules in foods, so wet foods get super hot, and dryer foods cook better with a cup of water in the microwave with it.  The microwave will save a hard loaf of bread or rolls and make them steamy and fresh if warmed with a cup of water.
